<refsect1 id="_description">
<title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<simpara>i3-sensible-editor is used by i3-nagbar(1) when you click on the edit button.</simpara>
<simpara>It tries to start one of the following (in that order):</simpara>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<simpara>
$VISUAL
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
$EDITOR
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
nano
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
nvim
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
vim
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
vi
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
emacs
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
pico
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
qe
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
mg
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
jed
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
gedit
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
mcedit
</simpara>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<simpara>
gvim
</simpara>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
<simpara>Please donâ€™t complain about the order: If the user has any preference, they will
have $VISUAL or $EDITOR set.</simpara>
